  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 3:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The great exception, blasphemy against the Holy Ghost.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς τὸν αἰῶνα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": hath not forgiveness ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for ever. Cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the fuller expression in Mt.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀλλʼ ἔνοχός ἐστιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but is guilty of. The negative is followed by a positive statement of similar import in Hebrew fashion.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αἰωνίου ἁμαρτήματος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of an eternal sin. As this is equivalent to “hath never forgiveness,” we must conceive of the sin as eternal in its guilt, not in itself as a sin. The idea is that of an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unpardonable",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " sin, not of a sin eternally repeating itself. Yet this may be the ultimate ground of unpardonableness: unforgivable because never repented of. But this thought is not necessarily contained in the expression.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
